OL,3,CElectricity and gas theft: The hidden
OL,4,Ccrime visible in your energy bill
OL,6,FFigures shared with ITV News have
OL,7,Frevealed a surge in cases of energy
OL,8,Ftheft across Britain, Consumer Editor
OL,9,FChris Choi reports
OL,11,FInsiders call it an invisible crime,
OL,12,Fbut energy theft becomes highly
OL,13,Fvisible in our energy bills.
OL,15,FIt's adding up to #50 per bill - a
OL,16,Ftotal of up to #1.4 billion to what
OL,17,Flaw-abiding customers pay. So today's
OL,18,Fnews that energy theft is on the rise
OL,19,Fis bad news for us all.
