OL,3,CElectricity and gas theft: The hidden
OL,4,Ccrime visible in your energy bill
OL,6,FFor gas, be vigilant for pipes that
OL,7,Fhave been bypassed, or look out of
OL,8,Fplace, or the use of rubber tubing.
OL,10,F"Gas theft, put simply, is where
OL,11,Fsomeone looks to take their gas for
OL,12,Ffree. Meter tampering is just one way
OL,13,Fin which people do this," Dave Garner,
OL,14,FDirector of Safety at Cadent, said.
OL,16,F"A gas meter should be flush against
OL,17,Fthe wall with the on off handle on the
OL,18,Fleft hand side. If you see anything
OL,19,Fdifferent to this, there is the
OL,20,Fpotential that someone has tampered
OL,21,Fwith their meter and is stealing gas."
